Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle, with gradual curve, of a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light red-brown. Rectangular stamp with club symbol.
Type series: KT119 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '92'; ink 'Duplicate'. Names, Kleumbrotos, Anaxandros.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (305B)
